        <h4 class="title is-4">Artist Statement</h4>
        <p>
        Humankind is challenged to make choices when designing and creating an environment for longevity. I have my own philosophies and conventions that drive my choices and decisions. The intended use of a piece influences every aspect of its surface – from decoration to texture and colour to shape. I’m motivated by the belief that a complete dinner table should contain three elements: utensils for food and drink, an equal range of serving ware, and any necessary holders for place cards and signage. The ensemble should reflect the mood and ambience of the environment it is a part of, whether it’s a boot-kickin’ barbecue on the back deck or a formal setting fit for the condo board; I want my knick-knacks and accents to evoke socialized use and a “How’s your Uncle Fester?” country club calm.
        </p>
