        <h4 class="title is-4">Artist Statement</h4>
        <p>
        “In shaping and firing clay, I like to depend on the incidental but also follow a set of rules. In this case, when building with clay there are just as many accidents as there are successes. It is the successes that I try to follow. Though I alter, omit or explode some rules, I continue to search for new rules or ways of existing within the rules set before me. I am currently questioning what are rules and what is happening in between what we call rules, what will be left as practice if we throw out the rules. By collapsing time through stratified and intuitive processes I lay basic forms that later will come together and intertwine. The transformation from basic forms evolves through sculpting, building, digging, cutting and burying. What come out of this are objects that suggest landscape, bodies, vessels, vistas and the unknown. In spite of how the work looks, the only moment it resembles is the moment it happened.
        "
